This paper discusses the performance of deep artificial neural networks in natural language processing tasks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the ability of these models to generalize and compose language, which are topics related to Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks for language tasks, which is a topic in Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
